comments: Williams (BOS) establishes himself in Williams' (CHI) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
LaVine (CHI) is moving alongside Tatum's (BOS) path and marginal body contact occurs during Tatum's drive.
Williams (CHI) initiates contact with Williams's (BOS) head during the drive and the contact affects his SQBR.
Horford (BOS) brings his hands towards Williams (CHI) and marginal contact occurs as Horford releases away from the contact.
Williams (CHI) extends his arm forward and does not maintain a legal guarding position when contact occurs with Tatum (BOS) during the rip-through.
LaVine (CHI) and Brown (BOS) briefly engage and disengage off ball.
Caruso (CHI) establishes himself in Brown's (BOS) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Horford (BOS) legally contests LaVine's (CHI) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Williams (BOS) and Caruso (CHI) come together at the same spot and marginal contact occurs as Williams deflects the ball away from Caruso.
Vucevic (CHI) briefly grasps Tatum's (BOS) arm and immediately releases him as the post entry pass is made.
Williams (CHI) and Tatum (BOS) briefly engage and disengage off ball.
Horford (BOS) establishes himself in Williams' (CHI) path and absorbs the contact.
Dosunmu (CHI) places his hand against Brown's (BOS) arm and marginal arm contact occurs during Brown's drive.
Dosunmu (CHI) legally contests Brown's (BOS) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Horford (BOS) and Vucevic (CHI) briefly engage and disengage during rebounding.
LaVine (CHI) brings his hand towards White's (BOS) torso and marginal contact occurs as LaVine releases away from the contact.
Williams (CHI) and Brown (BOS) briefly engage and disengage as they pursue the rebound.
Tatum (BOS) moves towards Dosunmu (CHI) and marginal contact occurs as they come together during the drive.
Vucevic (CHI) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Vucevic (CHI) legally contests Horford's (BOS) jump shot attempt.
Caruso (CHI) and White (BOS) come together in the lane and marginal contact occurs as they position themselves for a potential rebound.
White (CHI) establishes himself in Brown's (BOS) path and gives him a step to avoid contact.
Brown (BOS) and LaVine (CHI) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs as the screen is set.
Vucevic (CHI) establishes himself in Brown's (BOS) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Brown (BOS) brings his arm toward LaVine's (CHI) path and marginal contact occurs during LaVine's drive.
Brown (BOS) legally contests LaVine's (CHI) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Tatum (BOS) and Caruso (CHI) mutually engage and immediately disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Caruso (CHI) swipes his hand down and makes contact with Tatum's (BOS) arm as he defends the shot at the rim.
Brown (BOS) places his forearm to LaVine's (CHI) side during his drive to the basket and marginal body contact occurs.
Williams (BOS) brings his hand towards Williams (CHI) and marginal contact occurs as he pursues the rebound.

Caruso's (CHI) hand brushes Williams' (BOS) head/face, and the marginal contact occurs after Williams has secured possession.    Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
